    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-12-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-12-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="689"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d689">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.61248A/122</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Assistant Secretary of State</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sayre</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the South African Minister</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Close</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-19">December 19,
                            1936</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Minister</hi>: I wish to acknowledge with
                    thanks the receipt of your notes dated December 1 and December 15, 1936,<note
                        n="16" xml:id="d689fn16">Neither printed.</note> the former a recapitulation
                    of telegraphic exchanges with your government and the latter enclosing a copy of
                    a telegram informing us of the names of the Union Castle vessels which it is
                    proposed to equip for carrying grapes to Southampton in transit for New
                    York.</p>
                <p>I have conveyed all this information to appropriate officials in the Department
                    of Agriculture and I am informed that they are making their plans to send their
                    experts at the appropriate time.</p>
                <p>I am gratified that we have been able to make some progress in arriving at a
                    settlement of this question.</p>
                <p>Very sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi> B. <hi rend="smallcaps">Sayre</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
